### Acknowledgments & Upstream License

This project utilizes **Piper**, a fast, local neural text-to-speech system.

**Upstream Project:** [https://github.com/rhasspy/piper](https://github.com/rhasspy/piper)  
**Version Used:** `2023.11.14-2`  
**Upstream License:** MIT (Copyright (c) 2023 Michael Hansen)

We specifically use version `2023.11.14-2` of Piper as it is the most recent version released under the MIT License. We are grateful to the Rhasspy community and Michael Hansen for their incredible work on Piper.

---

### Third-Party Components

This project also incorporates code from **TextyMcSpeechy**, a cross-platform TTS engine.

**Project Source:** [https://github.com/domesticatedviking/TextyMcSpeechy](https://github.com/domesticatedviking/TextyMcSpeechy)  
**License:** MIT (Copyright (c) 2024 DomesticatedViking)

We are grateful to DomesticatedViking for the robust foundation provided by TextyMcSpeechy.

---

### Dependencies

This project uses the **Wyoming Protocol** for Home Assistant integration.

**Project Source:** [https://github.com/rhasspy/wyoming](https://github.com/rhasspy/wyoming)  
**License:** MIT (Copyright (c) The Open Home Foundation)

Wyoming is a peer-to-peer protocol for voice assistants maintained by the Open Home Foundation.

